## 3. Input Device Abstraction

### 3.1 Logical Action Vocabulary

The app MUST define a platform-agnostic set of named logical actions. Physical buttons map to these actions; UI handlers respond only to logical actions, never to raw key codes.

**Navigation Actions:**
- `nav.up`, `nav.down`, `nav.left`, `nav.right` — Directional focus movement
- `nav.confirm` — Select / OK / activate focused element
- `nav.back` — Back / cancel / dismiss overlay
- `nav.page_up`, `nav.page_down` — Jump one page in lists

**Player Actions:**
- `player.play_pause` — Toggle playback
- `player.seek_forward` — Seek forward (10s default)
- `player.seek_forward_large` — Seek forward large (30s)
- `player.seek_back` — Seek back (10s default)
- `player.seek_back_large` — Seek back large (30s)
- `player.volume_up`, `player.volume_down` — Volume adjustment
- `player.mute` — Toggle mute
- `player.fullscreen` — Toggle fullscreen
- `player.subtitles` — Cycle/select subtitle track
- `player.audio_track` — Cycle/select audio track
- `player.speed_up`, `player.speed_down` — Playback speed
- `player.stop` — Stop playback and exit player

**Content Actions:**
- `content.channel_up`, `content.channel_down` — Channel zapping
- `content.record` — Record current/focused program
- `content.favorite` — Toggle favorite on focused item
- `content.info` — Show details for focused item
- `content.watch_later` — Add to watchlist

**App Actions:**
- `app.home` — Navigate to home screen
- `app.guide` — Open EPG
- `app.dvr` — Open recordings
- `app.search` — Open search
- `app.settings` — Open settings
- `app.alpha_jump` — Jump to letter in lists

**Color Actions:**
- `color.red`, `color.green`, `color.yellow`, `color.blue` — Context-dependent color button actions

