### 3.3 Input Device Detection

- REQ-INPUT-01: The app MUST detect the currently active input device type (remote, gamepad, keyboard, mouse/air-mouse, touch)
- REQ-INPUT-02: Detection MUST be based on the most recent input event — D-pad key = remote/TV mode, pointer movement = mouse mode, touch = touch mode
- REQ-INPUT-03: When input mode changes, the UI MUST adapt within one frame (< 16ms)
- REQ-INPUT-04: Mouse cursor MUST appear when pointer moves, hide within 200ms when D-pad/gamepad is used
- REQ-INPUT-05: Focus ring MUST appear when D-pad/gamepad is used, transition to hover highlight when mouse is active
- REQ-INPUT-06: Controller hot-plug (connect/disconnect during use) MUST be handled gracefully — show "Controller disconnected" banner if playback is active

### 3.4 Analog Stick Navigation

- REQ-INPUT-07: Analog stick MUST produce timed-repeat item-by-item movement, not continuous scroll
- REQ-INPUT-08: Dead zone MUST be sufficient to prevent unintentional drift
- REQ-INPUT-09: Repeat rate MUST accelerate with sustained deflection — larger deflection = faster repeat
- REQ-INPUT-10: Analog triggers (L2/R2) MUST map to proportional seek speed in player — light press = slow seek, full press = fast seek

### 3.5 Button Legend Bar

- REQ-INPUT-11: A contextual button legend MUST be displayed on screen when D-pad, gamepad, or keyboard is the active input method
- REQ-INPUT-12: The legend MUST show only buttons relevant to the current screen and focused element
- REQ-INPUT-13: Legend icons MUST match the active input device (show Xbox glyphs for Xbox controller, PlayStation glyphs for PS controller, key labels for keyboard, color squares for remote)
- REQ-INPUT-14: The legend MUST update instantly when focus changes or screen changes
- REQ-INPUT-15: The legend MUST be hidden when touch or mouse is the active input (actions accessible via tap/context menus instead)
- REQ-INPUT-16: The legend bar MUST be translucent so it does not fully obscure content, and sized appropriately for the platform
- REQ-INPUT-17: The legend bar MUST NOT be focusable — it is informational only
- REQ-INPUT-18: The legend MUST NOT be the only way to discover actions — all actions MUST also be accessible via context menus

### 3.6 Color Button Semantics

Color buttons MUST follow consistent semantic categories:

| Color | Semantic | Examples | Never Use For |
|---|---|---|---|
| Red | Destructive / Recording / Alert | Delete, Stop recording, Cancel | Navigation, confirmation |
| Green | Primary positive action / Play | Play, Resume, Confirm, Go Live | Errors, deletion |
| Yellow | Toggle / Edit / Bookmark | Favorite, Add to list, Sort, Edit | Destructive actions |
| Blue | Informational / Secondary | Info, Details, Audio settings, Help | Primary actions |

These conventions align with the ETSI EN 300 468 European DVB broadcast standard — familiar to satellite/cable TV users.

**Context-specific mappings:**

| Screen | Red | Green | Yellow | Blue |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Channel list | Record | Play | Favorite | Info |
| EPG guide | Record | Watch/Jump | Reminder | Details |
| Recordings | Delete | Play | Edit | Info |
| Player (live) | Record | Go Live / Restart | Subtitles | Audio |
| Player (VOD) | — | — | Subtitles | Audio |
| VOD library | Remove | Play/Resume | Add to list | Info |

### 3.7 Number Key Channel Entry

- REQ-INPUT-19: Pressing digit keys MUST accumulate a channel number with a 2-second timeout between digits (max 4 digits)
- REQ-INPUT-20: A numeric overlay MUST appear showing digits as they are entered
- REQ-INPUT-21: After timeout or pressing OK/Select, the system MUST tune to the entered channel number
- REQ-INPUT-22: Backspace MUST clear the last digit; the overlay MUST dismiss on Back/Escape

### 3.8 Fast-Forward / Rewind Speed Cycling

- REQ-INPUT-23: First FF press = 2× speed; second = 4×; third = 8×; fourth = 16×; fifth = return to 1×
- REQ-INPUT-24: A speed indicator (e.g., ">> 4×" or "<< 8×") MUST be displayed prominently in the player OSD during trick play
- REQ-INPUT-25: Pressing Play during trick play MUST return to 1× playback at the current position

### 3.9 Custom Key Remapping

- REQ-INPUT-26: Users MUST be able to remap button assignments via a settings screen
- REQ-INPUT-27: The remapping UI MUST show a visual controller/remote diagram with labeled buttons
- REQ-INPUT-28: To remap: user selects an action, then presses the physical button to assign — the system captures the next button press
- REQ-INPUT-29: Remapping MUST warn before overriding critical actions (Back, Select)
- REQ-INPUT-30: "Reset to defaults" MUST be available per controller profile
- REQ-INPUT-31: Custom mappings MUST be exportable/importable as data files

### 3.10 Haptic Feedback

- REQ-INPUT-32: Gamepad rumble SHOULD provide subtle contextual feedback — lighter on focus move, moderate on selection, distinct on error
- REQ-INPUT-33: Haptic feedback MUST be configurable (on/off) in Settings → Accessibility
- REQ-INPUT-34: Haptic feedback MUST be suppressed during video playback to avoid distraction

### 3.11 HDMI-CEC

- REQ-INPUT-35: The app MUST handle CEC remote commands (D-pad, OK, Back, Play, Pause, Stop, FF, Rew, Channel Up/Down, Volume, Mute, Number keys, Color buttons)
- REQ-INPUT-36: CEC commands MUST map to the same logical actions as the primary remote
- REQ-INPUT-37: The app SHOULD support Wake-on-CEC (One Touch Play) for instant launch from TV remote

### 3.12 Air Mouse / Gyro Remotes (Pointer + D-pad Hybrids)

- REQ-INPUT-38: When pointer events arrive, the app MUST show a cursor and use hover-based highlighting
- REQ-INPUT-39: When D-pad events arrive while cursor is visible, the app MUST calculate the nearest focusable element from the cursor's current position in the pressed direction, focus it, and hide the cursor
- REQ-INPUT-40: When pointer moves after D-pad was active, the cursor MUST reappear at the center of the currently focused element (not jump to screen edge)

