## 5. Unified Series Library

### 5.1 Series-Specific Deduplication

- REQ-SER-01: Series MUST be deduplicated at the series level using the same three-tier cascade as movies
- REQ-SER-02: Episodes MUST be matched within a deduplicated series by season number + episode number
- REQ-SER-03: The same episode from different sources MUST be collapsed into one entry with a sources array (same pattern as movies)

### 5.2 Episode Source Matrix

- REQ-SER-04: The series detail page MUST show per-episode source availability
- REQ-SER-05: When an episode is available on multiple sources, quality badges MUST be shown per source
- REQ-SER-06: When an episode is available on only one source, that source MUST be indicated

**Visual representation (on the episode list):**

```
S01E01 "Pilot"           [Source A: 4K] [Source B: 1080p]   ✓ Watched
S01E02 "The Cat's Meow"  [Source A: 4K]                     ▶ Resume 23:45
S01E03 "Third Time"                     [Source B: 1080p]   ○ New
```

### 5.3 Series Progress Tracking

- REQ-SER-07: Watch progress MUST be tracked at the canonical episode level (tied to series TMDB ID + season + episode), NOT per source
- REQ-SER-08: Watching S01E03 on Source A MUST mark it as watched regardless of which source is used next
- REQ-SER-09: Resume position MUST be stored in milliseconds at the canonical level — resuming on Source B after starting on Source A MUST be seamless
- REQ-SER-10: "Continue Watching" on the home screen MUST show the series poster, next unwatched episode label (e.g., "S02E04"), and the best available source badge for that specific episode

### 5.4 Next Episode Logic

- REQ-SER-11: "Play Next Episode" MUST select the next unwatched episode by season/episode number
- REQ-SER-12: The source for the next episode MUST be auto-selected per the quality ranking (best quality available for that specific episode)
- REQ-SER-13: If the preferred source does not have the next episode but another source does, the system MUST transparently switch sources with a brief toast notification

