## 6. Multi-Source Live TV Experience

### 6.1 Unified Channel List

- REQ-LIVE-01: The default channel list MUST be unified across all sources with duplicates merged
- REQ-LIVE-02: Source attribution MUST NOT be visible by default — the unified list looks like one collection
- REQ-LIVE-03: A source filter bar MUST allow filtering to individual sources (see Section 7)
- REQ-LIVE-04: When the source filter is set to a specific source, the unmerged raw channel list from that source MUST be shown

### 6.2 Channel Deduplication

**Four-level matching pipeline:**

| Level | Method | Confidence |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `tvg-id` exact match (case-sensitive) | Highest |
| 2 | `tvg-id` normalized match (lowercase, strip dots/whitespace) | High |
| 3 | Channel name fuzzy match after normalization (strip quality suffixes, country codes, punctuation; token similarity > 85%) | Medium |
| 4 | Manual user override (merge or split) | Absolute |

**Channel name normalization:**
1. Lowercase
2. Strip quality suffixes (ordered, longest first): `4k, uhd, fhd, 1080p, 720p, hd, sd, plus, +1, h265, hevc, avc`
3. Strip country code suffixes in parentheses: `(US)`, `(UK)`, `(CA)`, etc.
4. Remove non-alphanumeric characters except hyphens and spaces
5. Collapse multiple spaces
6. Trim

- REQ-LIVE-05: Deduplication MUST be on by default, with a notification after first multi-source sync: "X duplicate channels merged — tap to review"
- REQ-LIVE-06: The merged channel MUST appear once with a stack icon indicating "available on N sources"
- REQ-LIVE-07: Tapping the stack icon MUST open a source picker showing: source name, quality badge (4K/FHD/HD/SD), stream health indicator (green/yellow/red), and currently selected source (checkmark)

### 6.3 Source Auto-Selection for Merged Channels

Priority order:
1. User's explicit per-channel preference (sticky, survives restarts)
2. Highest quality tier available
3. Within same quality: highest health score (based on recent success rate)
4. Within same health: lowest stream-start latency (measured historically)
5. Tie-break: user's global source priority order

### 6.4 Automatic Stream Failover

- REQ-LIVE-08: When a stream fails (connection error, timeout, or > N seconds buffer stall), the system MUST automatically try the next source in the merged group
- REQ-LIVE-09: Failover MUST be silent with a brief non-blocking toast: "Switched to [Source Name]" with undo option (3 seconds)
- REQ-LIVE-10: Failover MUST NOT restart from the beginning — resume at the playback position
- REQ-LIVE-11: 5 consecutive failures MUST be required before triggering failover (prevents flapping on transient network issues)
- REQ-LIVE-12: Failed streams MUST be recorded for health scoring; automatically retried after configurable dwell time (default 15 minutes)

### 6.5 EPG Merging

- REQ-LIVE-13: When multiple sources provide EPG for the same logical channel, the source with the highest priority (lowest sort_order) MUST win for overlapping time slots
- REQ-LIVE-14: EPG gaps MUST be filled from lower-priority sources (Source A has EPG for channel X, Source B doesn't — use Source A's EPG for both)
- REQ-LIVE-15: External public EPG sources (e.g., iptv-org/epg) SHOULD be supported as fallback EPG for channels without provider EPG

### 6.6 Category Normalization

- REQ-LIVE-16: When sources use different group names for semantically equivalent categories (Source A: "Sports", Source B: "Sport Channels"), the system SHOULD detect candidates for merging using keyword-based canonical category mapping
- REQ-LIVE-17: Category merges MUST be suggested to the user for confirmation, never silently applied
- REQ-LIVE-18: The suggested merge SHOULD appear in a "Source Setup Review" screen after adding a new source

### 6.7 Favorites Across Sources

- REQ-LIVE-19: A favorited channel MUST be favorited at the logical (merged) level — it persists regardless of which source is currently providing the stream
- REQ-LIVE-20: If a favorited channel's only source becomes unavailable, the favorite MUST remain (greyed out with "Unavailable" indicator)

### 6.8 Hidden Channels

- REQ-LIVE-21: Hiding a channel MUST offer two options: "Hide on [Source Name] only" or "Hide everywhere"
- REQ-LIVE-22: "Hide everywhere" MUST hide all instances across all sources

### 6.9 Channel Number Management

- REQ-LIVE-23: Each source's channels SHOULD retain their provider-assigned channel numbers by default
- REQ-LIVE-24: Optional unified numbering SHOULD be available by reserving number ranges per source (e.g., Source A = 1-999, Source B = 1000-1999)
- REQ-LIVE-25: Users SHOULD be able to assign custom channel numbers for favorites in a separate namespace

