## 7. Source-Aware Filtering & Search

### 7.1 Source Filter Bar

- REQ-FILT-01: A horizontal filter chip row MUST appear on channel list, movie library, series library, and search screens
- REQ-FILT-02: "All Sources" MUST be the first chip and the default selection
- REQ-FILT-03: Each source chip MUST show the source's user-assigned color dot and truncated name (max ~12 chars)
- REQ-FILT-04: Multiple source chips MAY be selected simultaneously (union of results)
- REQ-FILT-05: At 5+ sources, overflow chips MUST be accessible via horizontal scroll or a "More" chip that opens a selection sheet
- REQ-FILT-06: On TV, the filter bar MUST be a focus row navigable with Left/Right; Down returns to content
- REQ-FILT-07: Last-used source filter MUST be remembered per screen (channel list, movies, series, search)

### 7.2 Source Color-Coding

- REQ-FILT-08: Each source MUST have a user-assignable accent color from a palette of sufficiently distinguishable colors
- REQ-FILT-09: The source color MUST appear on: filter chips, source badges on content cards, source picker rows, and search result attribution

### 7.3 Search Across Sources

- REQ-FILT-10: Search MUST return results from ALL sources simultaneously by default
- REQ-FILT-11: Each search result MUST show source attribution badges (colored dots representing each source that has it)
- REQ-FILT-12: Duplicate results (same canonical entity on multiple sources) MUST be collapsed into one result with multi-source badges
- REQ-FILT-13: Source filter chips above search results MUST allow narrowing to specific sources
- REQ-FILT-14: Voice search MUST resolve to the best available source automatically without asking the user "which source?"

### 7.4 "Available On" Display on Cards

- REQ-FILT-15: In the default grid view: show only the best source's quality badge + a multi-source indicator if applicable (low clutter)
- REQ-FILT-16: In list view (if available): show source logo/dot row + quality badge (higher information density)
- REQ-FILT-17: On the detail page: full source list with quality badges, health indicators, and selection controls

---

## 8. Metadata Enrichment

### 8.1 TMDB Integration

- REQ-META-01: The system MUST integrate with TMDB (The Movie Database) to enrich movie and series metadata
- REQ-META-02: Enrichment MUST occur in the background after source sync, never blocking UI
- REQ-META-03: Enrichment MUST use a three-tier lookup: (1) external ID match via TMDB `/find` endpoint, (2) title + year search via `/search/movie` or `/search/tv`, (3) fuzzy title match as last resort

### 8.2 Metadata Hierarchy

When provider metadata conflicts with TMDB metadata:

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Poster, backdrop, overview, genres, cast, director, runtime, release date, ratings | TMDB (canonical, always wins) |
| Stream quality, audio tracks, subtitle tracks, container format | Provider (source-specific) |
| User manual override (corrected title, custom poster) | User preference (highest priority, never overwritten) |

- REQ-META-04: User manual metadata overrides MUST survive re-syncs and re-enrichment
- REQ-META-05: Placeholder content (shimmer skeleton or generic poster) MUST be shown while enrichment is pending

### 8.3 Enriched Content

| Data | Source | Use |
|---|---|---|
| Poster image | TMDB `/movie/{id}/images` | Grid cards, detail page |
| Backdrop image | TMDB backdrop | Hero banner, detail background |
| Synopsis / overview | TMDB | Detail page description |
| Cast & crew | TMDB `/movie/{id}/credits` | Detail page, tap-to-search |
| Genre tags | TMDB | Filtering, recommendation rows |
| User ratings | TMDB vote_average | Star rating display |
| YouTube trailers | TMDB `/movie/{id}/videos` | Detail page trailer button |
| Season/episode metadata | TMDB `/tv/{id}/season/{n}` | Series detail, episode list |
| Content ratings | TMDB `release_dates` / `content_ratings` | Parental controls |

- REQ-META-06: Trailer playback MUST be available on the detail page when TMDB provides a YouTube trailer key
- REQ-META-07: Cast members MUST be tappable to search for their other available content

### 8.4 Enrichment Performance

- REQ-META-08: TMDB API rate limits (40 requests per 10 seconds) MUST be respected with queueing and backoff
- REQ-META-09: For a library of 10,000 items, background enrichment MUST complete within a reasonable time without blocking the UI
- REQ-META-10: Enriched metadata MUST be cached locally with periodic refresh
- REQ-META-11: Images MUST be requested at appropriate sizes for the display context (thumbnail for grid, full-size for detail page), never full-original resolution

---

## Appendix: Accessibility on TV

### Screen Reader Support

- REQ-A11Y-TV-01: Every focusable element MUST have a meaningful semantic label (e.g., "Channel 32, BBC One, Now: EastEnders, Drama, 8:00 to 8:30 PM")
- REQ-A11Y-TV-02: Decorative elements (background images, shimmer placeholders) MUST be excluded from the semantic tree
- REQ-A11Y-TV-03: When focus moves rapidly through items, screen reader announcements MUST be debounced (500ms) to avoid overwhelming audio
- REQ-A11Y-TV-04: Dynamic content updates (hero panel changing on focus) MUST use polite live region semantics (announced after current speech completes)

### Switch Access

- REQ-A11Y-TV-05: All focusable items MUST be reachable in a logical linear scanning order for single-switch input
- REQ-A11Y-TV-06: Scanning speed MUST respect the system accessibility setting

### High Contrast Mode

- REQ-A11Y-TV-07: In high-contrast mode, focus ring MUST become more prominent — see "Standards & Compliance Reference" for contrast minimums
- REQ-A11Y-TV-08: Focus indicator contrast — see "Standards & Compliance Reference"

### Audio Navigation Cues

- REQ-A11Y-TV-09: Optional audio cues SHOULD be available: distinct sounds for focus move, selection confirm, and error/blocked action
- REQ-A11Y-TV-10: Audio cues MUST be off by default, enabled via Settings → Accessibility

---

## 9. Standards & Compliance Reference

> This section consolidates industry standards, platform requirements, and accessibility minimums referenced by requirements throughout this document. These are non-negotiable constraints from external authorities — not design recommendations. Implementations MUST meet these thresholds but MAY exceed them.

### 9.1 Focus Visibility (WCAG 2.2)

| Standard | Level | Minimum |
|---|---|---|
| Focus Visible (2.4.7) | AA | Focus indicator MUST have ≥ 3:1 contrast ratio against adjacent non-focused state |
| Focus Appearance (2.4.13) | AAA | Focus indicator area ≥ 2px perimeter; ≥ 3:1 contrast change |
| High Contrast Mode | AAA | Focus indicator ≥ 7:1 contrast when OS high-contrast is active |

### 9.2 TV Platform Minimums

These are vendor-mandated minimums from official platform design guidelines:

| Platform | Min Body Text | Min Interactive Element | Safe Area (Overscan) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Android TV (Google) | 24sp | 48×48dp | 48px H / 27px V (at 1080p) |
| tvOS (Apple) | ~24pt | 44×44pt | 60pt top/bottom, 80pt left/right |
| Fire TV (Amazon) | Same as Android TV | Same as Android TV | Same as Android TV |
| General 10-foot | Legible from 3m | Operable from 3m with D-pad | 5% all edges |

### 9.3 Gamepad Standards

| Standard | Requirement | Source |
|---|---|---|
| Xbox media app guidelines | A=Confirm, B=Back, LB/RB for page/channel | Microsoft |
| PlayStation media conventions | Cross=Confirm, Circle=Back (Western), L1/R1 for page | Sony |
| Android TV controller support | MUST handle both KEYCODE_BUTTON_* and AXIS_HAT_* for D-pad | Android TV developer docs |
| HID generic gamepad minimum | 4 face buttons + D-pad + 2 bumpers + 2 triggers + start/select | USB HID spec |

### 9.4 CEC (HDMI Consumer Electronics Control)

| Requirement | Source |
|---|---|
| MUST handle CEC User Control codes for: Select, D-pad, Play, Pause, Stop, FF, Rew, Channel±, Volume±, Mute, Color buttons, Number 0-9 | HDMI CEC spec |
| CEC button set is smaller than dedicated remotes — app MUST be fully operable with CEC-only input | Platform best practice |

### 9.5 Broadcast Caption Standards

| Standard | Requirement | Authority |
|---|---|---|
| CEA-608 | Legacy analog CC in MPEG-2 TS Line 21 data | FCC |
| CEA-708 | Digital CC in H.264/H.265 SEI NAL units; up to 63 services; rich styling | FCC |
| CVAA | Caption customization (font, size, color, opacity, background, edge style) MUST be user-configurable and persistent | FCC 21st Century CVAA |
| CVAA | Audio description tracks MUST be user-selectable | FCC 21st Century CVAA |

### 9.6 Color Button Convention (ETSI EN 300 468)

| Color | Semantic Category | Industry Precedent |
|---|---|---|
| Red | Destructive / Recording / Alert | European DVB broadcast |
| Green | Primary positive / Play / Confirm | European DVB broadcast |
| Yellow | Toggle / Edit / Bookmark | European DVB broadcast |
| Blue | Informational / Secondary / Help | European DVB broadcast |
