## 1. Offline & Network Degradation

### 1.1 Offline Feature Availability

| Feature | Offline Behavior |
|---|---|
| Downloaded VOD playback | Fully functional |
| Cached EPG browsing | Show last-fetched data with staleness indicator |
| Watch history / Continue Watching | Read from local database |
| Favorites / Watchlist | Read from local database |
| App settings | Fully functional |
| Search across cached metadata | Functional, results limited to cached items (indicate scope) |
| Bookmarks / playback positions | Read from local database |
| Live TV (IPTV) | Blocked — show specific error |
| VOD browsing (non-cached) | Show cached data if available, otherwise show empty state with explanation |
| Media server content | Show last-synced metadata; play only if downloaded |

- REQ-OFF-01: The app MUST never show a blank screen when offline — navigation chrome and cached content MUST remain accessible
- REQ-OFF-02: When completely offline, a persistent banner (not a toast) MUST indicate the offline state
- REQ-OFF-03: EPG data MUST be cached locally for at least 7 days; a staleness indicator MUST appear when data is older than 24 hours
- REQ-OFF-04: Poster images and thumbnails for Favorites, Watchlist, Continue Watching, and downloaded content MUST be cached for offline browsing
- REQ-OFF-05: Image cache MUST use LRU eviction with a configurable size limit

### 1.2 Error Message Differentiation

The app MUST distinguish between different network failure modes and present contextually appropriate messages:

| Condition | Detection | Message Tone |
|---|---|---|
| Device offline (no network interface) | OS network state API | "You're offline. Connect to Wi-Fi or mobile data to stream." |
| Internet unreachable (connected but no route) | Probe to a known public endpoint fails | "Your internet connection isn't working. Check your router." |
| Source/provider down (internet works, source doesn't) | Source endpoint fails while others succeed | "[Source Name] is unavailable right now. Your internet is working fine." |
| Specific channel/stream failure | One stream fails while other sources work | "This channel is currently unavailable. Try another or check back later." |

- REQ-OFF-06: Error messages MUST never blame the user; MUST state what happened + what to do
- REQ-OFF-07: Error messages MUST be contextual — the same underlying error produces different wording depending on what the user was doing (starting a channel vs background EPG sync)
- REQ-OFF-08: Background operations (EPG refresh, metadata enrichment) MUST retry silently — never interrupt the user with a modal for non-critical background failures

### 1.3 Network Quality Adaptation

- REQ-OFF-09: The player MUST support adaptive bitrate switching, automatically adjusting quality based on network conditions
- REQ-OFF-10: A quality selector MUST be available in the player showing the current active resolution within the "Auto" option (e.g., "Auto · 1080p")
- REQ-OFF-11: Users MUST be able to set a maximum quality cap that persists per-profile (for bandwidth-limited environments)
- REQ-OFF-12: On first cellular data stream, a one-time prompt MUST ask the user to choose: continue at current quality, switch to data saver, or restrict to Wi-Fi only
- REQ-OFF-13: Data saver mode MUST have a visible persistent indicator in the player
- REQ-OFF-14: When quality drops significantly mid-stream, a brief passive indicator MUST appear (not a modal — a small badge change for a few seconds)

### 1.4 Download for Offline (VOD)

- REQ-OFF-15: Users MUST be able to download VOD content for offline playback on mobile and tablet platforms
- REQ-OFF-16: Download quality selection MUST be available (multiple tiers with estimated file size shown before confirming)
- REQ-OFF-17: Downloads MUST default to Wi-Fi only, with an explicit one-time override for cellular
- REQ-OFF-18: Interrupted downloads MUST resume from where they left off (partial download preserved)
- REQ-OFF-19: Smart Downloads SHOULD auto-delete watched episodes and auto-download the next, Wi-Fi only
- REQ-OFF-20: Downloaded content MUST show expiry date; a warning MUST appear before expiry with a "Refresh" action
- REQ-OFF-21: Storage management UI MUST show: per-title size, total usage vs available, sortable by size/date/expiry, and a one-tap cleanup for watched/expired content
- REQ-OFF-22: Downloads are a mobile/tablet feature — TV and web platforms need not support offline downloads

### 1.5 Connection Recovery

- REQ-OFF-23: When network returns after an outage, the app MUST auto-reconnect streams using exponential backoff (immediate → 2s → 5s → 15s → 30s; stop after 5 minutes and show manual retry)
- REQ-OFF-24: VOD MUST resume from exact position after reconnect — never restart from the beginning
- REQ-OFF-25: Live TV MUST resume at the live edge after reconnect (not attempt to show missed content)
- REQ-OFF-26: A brief "Reconnecting..." overlay MUST appear during attempts; "Reconnected" confirmation auto-dismisses
- REQ-OFF-27: All user actions performed while offline (position updates, favorites changes, ratings) MUST be queued in a durable local outbox and replayed on reconnect
- REQ-OFF-28: Conflict resolution for offline changes: last-write-wins by timestamp for positions; union merge for favorites/watchlist

---

## 2. Multi-Device Handoff & Casting

### 2.1 Cross-Device Position Sync

- REQ-HAND-01: Playback position MUST be written to the backend at regular intervals during active playback, plus on pause, seek, app background, and app terminate
- REQ-HAND-02: Position accuracy MUST be within the last sync interval (no more than 30 seconds behind actual)
- REQ-HAND-03: All connected devices MUST be notified of position changes in near-real-time (push via WebSocket for connected devices; pull on app lifecycle events as consistency check)
- REQ-HAND-04: "Continue Watching" MUST reflect cross-device progress — content paused on phone appears with correct position on TV
- REQ-HAND-05: When resuming content on a different device, the system SHOULD show: "You were watching on [device] at [timestamp]. Resume?" with Resume and Start Over options

### 2.2 Device Linking & Management

- REQ-HAND-06: Primary linking: account-based auto-linking — all devices signed into the same account are implicitly linked with no pairing step
- REQ-HAND-07: Secondary linking: QR code + numeric PIN displayed simultaneously on TV for device pairing (codes expire after a reasonable time; show countdown)
- REQ-HAND-08: Same-network auto-discovery MUST detect other app instances on the local network via service advertisement (mDNS or equivalent)
- REQ-HAND-09: Discovery MUST require explicit accept/reject on the target device to prevent session hijacking
- REQ-HAND-10: Device management screen MUST show: device name, type icon, last active timestamp, approximate location, and currently-streaming indicator
- REQ-HAND-11: "Remove device" and "Sign out all devices" actions MUST be available with confirmation

### 2.3 Concurrent Stream Limits

- REQ-HAND-12: Stream limits MUST be enforced server-side at session creation
- REQ-HAND-13: When the limit is exceeded, the error MUST show which devices are currently streaming and offer "End stream on [Device]" without requiring the user to navigate to device management

### 2.4 Casting (Chromecast / AirPlay / DLNA)

- REQ-HAND-14: A cast/route picker icon MUST appear in the player and on content detail pages when cast-capable devices are detected on the network
- REQ-HAND-15: During a cast session, a persistent mini-player MUST appear on the sender device in all non-player screens (thumbnail, title, play/pause, stop cast)
- REQ-HAND-16: Mini-player state MUST stay in sync with the receiver — changes from other senders or the receiver's own controls are reflected
- REQ-HAND-17: When the sender app moves to background, the cast session MUST continue on the receiver (suspend, not end)
- REQ-HAND-18: When the receiver disconnects (TV powered off, network lost), the sender MUST save last position and offer "Continue here" to resume locally
- REQ-HAND-19: Volume buttons on the sender device MUST control the receiver's volume during an active cast session (not the phone speaker)
- REQ-HAND-20: Queue management during cast MUST allow add, remove, and reorder without interrupting current playback
- REQ-HAND-21: DLNA/UPnP SHOULD be supported as a supplementary casting method for local media to legacy smart TVs (no DRM content via DLNA)

### 2.5 Companion / Second Screen

- REQ-HAND-22: The phone app SHOULD be usable as a remote control for the TV app over the local network (D-pad, keyboard input, voice search relay)
- REQ-HAND-23: Keyboard input from the companion phone MUST relay keystrokes to the TV app for search and text entry (eliminating TV on-screen keyboard)
- REQ-HAND-24: During companion mode, the phone MAY display supplementary info: now-playing metadata, chapter list, next episode card

### 2.6 Watch Together

- REQ-HAND-25: Synchronized group viewing MUST be supported for VOD and DVR content (live TV is exempt — broadcast clock provides inherent sync)
- REQ-HAND-26: Sync MUST be server-coordinated with gradual drift correction (speed adjustment for drift < 3s, hard seek only for drift > 3s)
- REQ-HAND-27: The session host controls play/pause/seek by default; all participants see who else is in the session
- REQ-HAND-28: In-session text chat and emoji reactions MUST be supported

---

## 3. Notification System

### 3.1 Notification Types

| Category | Examples | Delivery | Default |
|---|---|---|---|
| Recording lifecycle | Starting, complete, failed, conflict, storage threshold | Local (native DVR) or Push (cloud DVR) | ON |
| Content updates | New episode available, new movie added, content expiring | Push (after server-side library diff) | Episodes ON, Movies OFF |
| EPG reminders | "Show X starts in 15 min on Channel Y" | Local (scheduled on device) | ON (when user sets reminder) |
| Source status | Sync failed, source offline, credentials expired | Local (device detection) or Push | ON (failures only) |
| Social / Watch party | Invitation, party starting soon | Push (real-time) | ON |
| App & System | Update available, database maintenance, security alerts | Push or Local | ON |

### 3.2 Delivery Requirements

- REQ-NOTIF-01: The app MUST maintain an in-app notification centre as the canonical notification store across ALL platforms — this is the only reliable notification surface on TV platforms
- REQ-NOTIF-02: On TV (Android TV, Fire TV, tvOS), all notifications MUST be delivered as in-app overlays or via the notification centre — system notification shade is unreliable on TV
- REQ-NOTIF-03: Notifications MUST be grouped by category to avoid overload; batch multiple same-category notifications from a single sync cycle into one summary
- REQ-NOTIF-04: Each notification MUST carry a deep link to the relevant screen (recording → playback, source error → source settings, new episode → series detail)
- REQ-NOTIF-05: Notification bell/badge MUST be accessible from the main navigation on all form factors

### 3.3 Notification Preferences

- REQ-NOTIF-06: Per-category toggles MUST be available in per-profile notification settings
- REQ-NOTIF-07: Quiet hours MUST be configurable per-profile (time window during which non-critical notifications are deferred); critical alerts (storage full, recording failed) bypass quiet hours
- REQ-NOTIF-08: Child profiles MUST receive only content and reminder alerts relevant to their profile — no system or social notifications
- REQ-NOTIF-09: Notification history MUST be retained for 30 days with mark-as-read and dismiss actions

---

## 4. Deep Linking & Voice Assistants

### 4.1 Deep Link Structure

The app MUST register both a custom URI scheme and equivalent HTTPS universal/app links for all navigable destinations:

| Target | Deep Link Pattern |
|---|---|
| Channel playback | `{scheme}://channel/{channel-id}` |
| EPG programme | `{scheme}://channel/{channel-id}/epg/{entry-id}` |
| VOD detail | `{scheme}://vod/{vod-id}` |
| VOD playback at position | `{scheme}://vod/{vod-id}/play?position={seconds}` |
| Series episode | `{scheme}://series/{series-id}/season/{n}/episode/{n}` |
| Recording | `{scheme}://recording/{recording-id}` |
| Search | `{scheme}://search?q={query}&type={live\|vod\|series}` |
| Settings section | `{scheme}://settings/{section}` |
| Watch party join | `{scheme}://watchparty/{party-id}` |
| Playlist import | `{scheme}://playlist/import?url={encoded-url}` |

- REQ-LINK-01: A single deep link router MUST handle all incoming URIs on all platforms
- REQ-LINK-02: If the user is not authenticated when a deep link arrives, the app MUST redirect to login, store the pending link, and resume navigation after authentication
- REQ-LINK-03: Playback deep links with a `position` parameter MUST seek directly without prompting
- REQ-LINK-04: Unknown or invalid entity IDs MUST show a graceful "not found" screen, not crash

### 4.2 Voice Assistant Integration

- REQ-VOICE-01: The app MUST register as a media playback destination for the platform's voice assistant (Google Assistant on Android TV, Alexa on Fire TV, Siri on tvOS)
- REQ-VOICE-02: Voice commands for "Play [channel/title] on [app name]" MUST resolve to the content and begin playback immediately without intermediate screens
- REQ-VOICE-03: Standard transport commands (pause, resume, rewind, fast-forward, stop) MUST be handled via the platform's media session API
- REQ-VOICE-04: "What's on [channel]?" MUST open EPG filtered to that channel
- REQ-VOICE-05: "Resume what I was watching" MUST resolve from watch history and seek to last position
- REQ-VOICE-06: The app SHOULD publish content to platform home screen recommendation channels (Google TV Watch Next, Apple TV Top Shelf) with deep link intents

### 4.3 Receiving Shared Content

- REQ-LINK-05: The app MUST register as a handler for M3U/M3U8 files opened from file managers, routing to the playlist import flow
- REQ-LINK-06: The app MUST register as a handler for shared `text/plain` content that contains stream URLs, routing to the import flow
- REQ-LINK-07: The app MUST register as a handler for `video/*` files, offering direct playback without requiring library import

### 4.4 Outgoing Share

- REQ-LINK-08: Every channel and VOD item MUST have a "Share" action that generates a universal link
- REQ-LINK-09: The universal link's landing page MUST serve Open Graph and social card metadata (title, poster image, description) for rich previews on social platforms
- REQ-LINK-10: On TV, sharing MUST display a QR code that the recipient scans with their phone

---

## 5. Error States & Recovery

### 5.1 Error Taxonomy

Errors fall into these domains, each with distinct user messaging and recovery strategy:

| Domain | Examples | Recovery Class |
|---|---|---|
| Network | Offline, slow connection, DNS failure, timeout, captive portal | Degrade to cached content; retry with backoff |
| Source/Provider | Server down, credentials expired, rate limited, API changed | Circuit breaker; serve cached data; prompt re-auth |
| Stream/Playback | Codec unsupported, DRM failure, geo-blocked, stream ended, buffering | Offer alternatives (external player, different source); lower quality |
| Storage | Disk full, database corrupt, cache invalid | Pause writes; notify with storage management; rebuild from sources |
| Auth/Profile | PIN wrong, session expired, account suspended, parental block | Progressive lockout; prompt re-login; PIN override |
| Player | Decoder crash, audio device lost, display disconnected | Auto-restart at checkpoint; pause on device loss |
| System | Out of memory, background killed, update required | Evict caches; checkpoint and restore on relaunch |

### 5.2 Error Message Requirements

- REQ-ERR-01: All error messages MUST use plain language with two parts: what happened + what to do next
- REQ-ERR-02: User-fixable errors (credentials, network) MUST use a warning visual treatment; system errors (server down) MUST use a neutral informational treatment; critical errors (disk full, data risk) MUST use an urgent treatment
- REQ-ERR-03: Error screens MUST include at least one action button: "Try Again", "Go Back", "Manage Storage", or "Sign In Again" as appropriate
- REQ-ERR-04: "Contact Support" MUST only appear for errors that are definitively not user-fixable
- REQ-ERR-05: Error illustrations MUST match the app's visual style; avoid generic stock error icons

### 5.3 Crash Recovery

- REQ-ERR-06: Playback position MUST be checkpointed to persistent storage at regular intervals during active playback
- REQ-ERR-07: On crash/forced-close, the app MUST restore to the last screen on relaunch (excluding the player — to avoid re-crash loops)
- REQ-ERR-08: An incomplete-playback flag MUST trigger a "Continue watching?" prompt on relaunch
- REQ-ERR-09: Database integrity MUST be checked on startup after an unclean shutdown; if corrupt, attempt automatic recovery; if recovery fails, rebuild from remote sources with user notification
- REQ-ERR-10: The corrupt database file MUST be preserved (moved to backup path) for diagnostic purposes before rebuilding

### 5.4 Retry & Fallback

- REQ-ERR-11: All transient error retries MUST use exponential backoff with jitter to prevent thundering herd
- REQ-ERR-12: Each source/provider MUST have an independent circuit breaker: closed (normal) → open (reject and serve cached) → half-open (probe one request)
- REQ-ERR-13: When a source is in circuit-breaker-open state, the app MUST serve the most recent cached data with a staleness indicator — never a blank screen
- REQ-ERR-14: Non-critical background operations (metadata enrichment, EPG refresh, cloud sync) MUST use a durable retry queue that persists across app restarts; discard after maximum lifetime

### 5.5 Player Error Recovery

- REQ-ERR-15: If the media decoder crashes, the player MUST auto-restart at the last checkpointed position
- REQ-ERR-16: If the audio output device disconnects (headphones unplugged, Bluetooth lost), playback MUST pause immediately
- REQ-ERR-17: If a stream fails and the content is available from another source (merged channel), the system MUST auto-failover per the rules in SRS-ADDENDUM-2 Section 6.4
- REQ-ERR-18: A watchdog MUST detect hung playback states (no new frame rendered for an extended period during active playback) and trigger player subsystem restart

---

## 6. Performance & Resource Budgets

### 6.1 Startup Performance

- REQ-PERF-01: The app MUST reach an interactive state (home screen with content visible) as fast as possible — every second of delay correlates with measurable retention loss
- REQ-PERF-02: Startup MUST load eagerly: auth state, user profile, cached home screen data. Lazy-load: remote EPG refresh, artwork updates, recommendation refresh, source health checks
- REQ-PERF-03: Skeleton screens MUST appear immediately while data loads — shimmer animation at the correct layout dimensions; replace cells individually as data arrives
- REQ-PERF-04: If initialization takes longer than expected, skeleton screens MUST replace the splash screen — users need to see structure

### 6.2 Memory & Resources

- REQ-PERF-05: Memory usage MUST stay within platform budget constraints (TV devices typically have limited RAM — the app must be designed for the lowest-common-denominator target)
- REQ-PERF-06: Image cache MUST use LRU eviction with a size-based (bytes) cap — two tiers: in-memory (fast, small) + disk (slower, larger)
- REQ-PERF-07: On memory pressure signals from the OS, the app MUST progressively release resources: reduce image cache → clear image cache → release non-essential in-memory state
- REQ-PERF-08: Video decoder hardware slots MUST be released promptly when navigating away from the player (finite decoder slots on most TV hardware)
- REQ-PERF-09: When the app moves to background, artwork fetching MUST pause, image cache MUST be reduced, and non-essential timers MUST stop

### 6.3 Battery & Power (Mobile)

- REQ-PERF-10: Wake locks MUST be held only during active audio/video playback; released immediately on pause/stop
- REQ-PERF-11: Background tasks (metadata sync, EPG refresh) MUST be batched and constrained to network-available + charging when possible
- REQ-PERF-12: Screen-on prevention MUST be active only during video playback; released on pause so the screen can dim naturally

### 6.4 Storage

- REQ-PERF-13: Cache management MUST auto-cleanup when usage exceeds a configurable threshold; prompt the user when device storage is critically low
- REQ-PERF-14: Database MUST be periodically compacted; old data pruned (EPG entries older than 14 days, watch history older than 12 months)
- REQ-PERF-15: Temporary files MUST be cleaned up on every startup

### 6.5 Rendering

- REQ-PERF-16: Navigation and scrolling MUST maintain smooth frame rates — only animate `transform` and `opacity` properties during transitions
- REQ-PERF-17: Lists with many items MUST use virtual/windowed rendering (only render visible items + buffer)
- REQ-PERF-18: Image loading MUST use a three-stage pipeline: placeholder (immediate) → low-res thumbnail → full resolution — with no layout shift between stages
- REQ-PERF-19: Entrance animations MUST be brief; OSD overlays MUST appear quickly

### 6.6 Network Performance

- REQ-PERF-20: Time-to-first-frame for live channel zapping MUST be minimized — pre-buffering adjacent channels is the recommended approach
- REQ-PERF-21: Home screen content rows MUST load in parallel (featured, continue watching, live now, recommendations are independent data)
- REQ-PERF-22: For series, the next episode SHOULD begin buffering before the current episode completes
- REQ-PERF-23: Image prefetch MUST be limited to avoid saturating bandwidth that delays critical playback requests

---

## 7. Home Screen Widgets & System Integration

### 7.1 Widget Types

| Widget | Content | Platforms |
|---|---|---|
| Now Playing | Current channel/programme, artwork, play/pause control | Mobile (Android, iOS) |
| Quick Channels | Grid of pinned channel shortcuts — tap to launch directly into playback | Mobile (Android, iOS) |
| Continue Watching | Carousel of in-progress VOD items with poster and progress | Mobile (Android, iOS) |
| Next Up | Next EPG event for a favourite channel with countdown | Mobile (Android, iOS) |
| DVR Status | Next scheduled recording, status badge | Mobile (Android, iOS) |

- REQ-WIDGET-01: Widget updates MUST be driven by events from the playback service, not by periodic polling (to preserve battery)
- REQ-WIDGET-02: Interactive widgets (where platform supports) MUST allow play/pause control without launching the full app
- REQ-WIDGET-03: All widget tap targets MUST deep link directly to the relevant content
- REQ-WIDGET-04: On iOS, a Live Activity SHOULD display current programme and progress during active playback (lock screen + Dynamic Island)

### 7.2 System Media Controls

- REQ-WIDGET-05: The app MUST integrate with the platform's system media controls on ALL platforms — providing artwork, title, and transport controls (play/pause, next/previous)
- REQ-WIDGET-06: System media controls MUST be active during both video and audio-only playback
- REQ-WIDGET-07: Metadata in system controls MUST include: programme/episode title, channel/series name, and artwork (poster or channel logo)

### 7.3 Platform Home Screen Integration

- REQ-WIDGET-08: On TV platforms (Android TV/Google TV, Fire TV), the app SHOULD publish content to the platform's recommendation/home screen rows (Continue Watching, Featured) with deep link intents
- REQ-WIDGET-09: The "Watch Next" / "Continue Watching" platform channel MUST be updated in real-time as users pause or complete content

---

## 8. Sharing & Social Features

### 8.1 Content Sharing

- REQ-SHARE-01: Every channel and VOD item MUST have a shareable deep link in universal link format
- REQ-SHARE-02: Shared links MUST render social preview cards (title, poster, description) when pasted into social media or messaging apps
- REQ-SHARE-03: On TV, sharing MUST present a QR code that encodes the deep link for phone scanning
- REQ-SHARE-04: "Copy Link" MUST be available as a non-network action alongside the platform share sheet

### 8.2 Household Social

- REQ-SHARE-05: Profiles within a household SHOULD support a shared watchlist where all profiles can add items and vote to prioritize
- REQ-SHARE-06: "Recommend to [profile]" SHOULD allow one profile to suggest content to another within the household without modifying their watchlist directly

---

## 9. Audio-Only / Radio Experience

### 9.1 Radio Stream Detection

- REQ-RADIO-01: The app MUST detect audio-only streams via: `radio="true"` M3U attribute, audio-only MIME type, codec inspection (no video track), and group-title heuristics (contains "Radio", "Music", "Audio")
- REQ-RADIO-02: Radio channels MUST be visually distinguished in the channel list with a radio/audio icon
- REQ-RADIO-03: Radio channels SHOULD be grouped in a dedicated "Radio" section or tab

### 9.2 Audio-Only Playback UI

- REQ-RADIO-04: Audio-only streams MUST render without a video surface — show station logo, programme name (from EPG if available), and an animated visual element (waveform or blurred artwork)
- REQ-RADIO-05: Audio playback MUST continue with the screen off and with other apps in the foreground on all mobile platforms (requires platform-appropriate background audio configuration)
- REQ-RADIO-06: Lock screen and system media controls MUST display station artwork, programme/station name, and playback controls during audio playback

### 9.3 Car Integration

- REQ-RADIO-07: The app SHOULD expose radio channels as a browsable media tree for Android Auto integration
- REQ-RADIO-08: The app SHOULD expose radio channels for Apple CarPlay (audio content only — no video on CarPlay)
- REQ-RADIO-09: Bluetooth AVRCP metadata (station name, programme title) MUST be populated via the platform's media session API (automatic when system media controls are properly integrated)

### 9.4 Audio Features

- REQ-RADIO-10: A sleep timer MUST be available for audio playback with preset durations and a custom option, displayed in the notification/media controls
- REQ-RADIO-11: Playback speed controls SHOULD be available for recorded/on-demand audio content (not for live radio streams — speed > 1x causes desync)

---

## 10. Theming & Whitelabel

### 10.1 Theme Modes

- REQ-THEME-01: The app MUST support Dark, Light, and System-follow theme modes
- REQ-THEME-02: Users MUST be able to select a custom accent color, persisted per profile
- REQ-THEME-03: On platforms that support it, the app SHOULD adopt the OS-provided dynamic color system (e.g., Material You wallpaper extraction on Android)
- REQ-THEME-04: Profile switching MUST animate a smooth theme transition when profiles have different accent colors

### 10.2 Design Token Architecture

- REQ-THEME-05: All visual values (colors, corner radii, typography scale, spacing) MUST be parameterized through a single design-token layer — no visual values hardcoded in component code
- REQ-THEME-06: All theme configurations (including custom accent colors) MUST comply with contrast requirements from the Standards & Compliance section — validate luminance at design-token generation time

### 10.3 Whitelabel / Provider Branding

- REQ-THEME-07: A whitelabel build system MUST accept a brand configuration (app name, bundle ID, icon, splash screen, color scheme, logo URL, default server URL, terms of service URL, privacy URL, and feature flags) and produce a distinctly branded build without code changes
- REQ-THEME-08: Feature flags in the brand configuration MUST individually enable/disable: DVR, VOD browsing, media server integration, social/sharing features, radio section
- REQ-THEME-09: The brand configuration MUST be the single source of truth for all branding — no brand assets scattered across code

### 10.4 Dynamic / Seasonal Theming

- REQ-THEME-10: Seasonal or event-based theme overlays SHOULD be loadable from a remote configuration without requiring an app update
- REQ-THEME-11: Time-of-day color shifts (warmer tones in evening, reduced blue light at night) MAY be offered as an opt-in user preference
