## 4. Media Server API Enhancements

The current SRS covers basic Plex/Emby/Jellyfin auth and content fetching. Research reveals significant API capabilities that should be specified.

### 4.1 Playback Negotiation (All Three Servers)

**Critical missing capability:** The client must negotiate playback format with the server via DeviceProfile.

- REQ-MS-01: Client MUST send a DeviceProfile to the server specifying supported codecs, containers, and subtitle methods
- REQ-MS-02: Server returns a PlaybackInfo decision: Direct Play (serve file as-is) → Direct Stream (remux to compatible container) → Transcode (HLS stream)
- REQ-MS-03: Client MUST implement the three-tier cascade: prefer Direct Play → fall back to Direct Stream → fall back to Transcode
- REQ-MS-04: Client MUST report PlaybackStart, PlaybackProgress (every 10 seconds), and PlaybackStopped to the server for watch position tracking

**Plex-specific:** Decision via `GET /video/:/transcode/universal/decision` with `X-Plex-Client-Profile-Extra` header
**Emby/Jellyfin:** Decision via `POST /Items/{itemId}/PlaybackInfo` with DeviceProfile JSON body

**Critical bug source:** Emby/Jellyfin use `PositionTicks` (100-nanosecond units: `ms * 10000`). Plex uses milliseconds. Wrong unit = resume position off by 10,000x.

### 4.2 Content Discovery APIs

| API | Plex | Emby | Jellyfin |
|---|---|---|---|
| Home screen hubs | `GET /hubs` | `GET /Users/{id}/Suggestions` | `GET /Users/{id}/Suggestions` |
| Continue watching | `GET /library/onDeck` | `GET /Users/{id}/Items/Resume` | `GET /Users/{id}/Items/Resume` |
| Recently added | `GET /library/recentlyAdded` | `GET /Users/{id}/Items/Latest` | `GET /Users/{id}/Items/Latest` |
| Similar/related | `GET /library/metadata/{id}/related` | `GET /Items/{id}/Similar` | `GET /Items/{id}/Similar` |
| Next episode | Built into On Deck | `GET /Shows/{id}/NextUp` | `GET /Shows/NextUp` |
| Extras/trailers | `GET /library/metadata/{id}/extras` | Yes | Yes |
| Collections | Yes (smart + manual) | Yes | Yes |
| Playlists | Yes | Yes | Yes |

- REQ-MS-05: Client MUST render server-provided "hubs" / suggestion rows on the home screen alongside IPTV content
- REQ-MS-06: "Continue Watching" MUST merge media server resume items with IPTV watch history into a single unified row

### 4.3 Live TV & DVR (Media Servers)

All three servers support Live TV with tuners and DVR:

- REQ-MS-07: Client SHOULD support media server Live TV channels (via tuner + EPG) as an additional source alongside IPTV
- REQ-MS-08: Client SHOULD support media server DVR scheduling (single timer + series timer) via the server's LiveTv API
- REQ-MS-09: Media server recordings SHOULD appear alongside IPTV DVR recordings in a unified recordings view

### 4.4 Subtitles & Chapters

| Feature | Plex | Emby | Jellyfin |
|---|---|---|---|
| Embedded subtitles | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| External sidecar | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Subtitle upload | No | No | Yes (`POST /Videos/{id}/Subtitles`) |
| Remote subtitle search | Plugin | Plugin | `GET /Items/{id}/RemoteSearch/Subtitles` |
| Chapter markers | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Chapter images | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Trickplay (scrub thumbnails) | Yes | Yes | Yes (native in v10.9+) |
| Intro detection/skip | Yes (Plex Pass) | Plugin | Yes (intro-skipper plugin) |
| Credits detection | Yes (Plex Pass) | Plugin | Yes (intro-skipper plugin) |

- REQ-MS-10: Client MUST request chapter data and present chapter scrubber in the seek bar
- REQ-MS-11: Client MUST request trickplay/scrub thumbnail images for seek preview
- REQ-MS-12: Client MUST query intro/credits timestamps and present Skip buttons (Plex native markers; Jellyfin via intro-skipper plugin endpoint)
- REQ-MS-13: Client SHOULD support Jellyfin subtitle search and download from within the player

### 4.5 Real-Time Updates (WebSocket)

- REQ-MS-14: Client MUST maintain WebSocket connection to each media server for real-time library change events
- REQ-MS-15: On `LibraryChanged` / `UserDataChanged` events, client MUST refresh affected content without full reload
- REQ-MS-16: WebSocket reconnect MUST use exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s → max 30s)

### 4.6 Image Loading

- REQ-MS-17: Client MUST request images at target display dimensions via server-side transcoding (never full-size originals)
- REQ-MS-18: Image requests MUST include cache-buster tag from item metadata for proper HTTP caching
- REQ-MS-19: Request at 2x logical pixel density for HiDPI displays

**Plex:** `GET /photo/:/transcode?url={path}&width={w}&height={h}`
**Emby/Jellyfin:** `GET /Items/{id}/Images/{type}?fillWidth={w}&fillHeight={h}&quality=90&tag={tag}`

### 4.7 Unified Multi-Server Architecture

- REQ-MS-20: A `MediaServerInterface` abstraction MUST normalize all three server APIs behind common domain types
- REQ-MS-21: All content from media servers MUST carry `serverId` + `serverType` for proper routing
- REQ-MS-22: Playback session lifecycle (negotiate → start → progress → stop) MUST be server-type-aware

### 4.8 Watch Together / SyncPlay

- REQ-MS-23: Client SHOULD support Jellyfin SyncPlay (synchronized group watch, free)
- REQ-MS-24: Client SHOULD support Plex Watch Together (Plex Pass feature)
- REQ-MS-25: SyncPlay requires WebSocket-based time synchronization with clock offset estimation

### 4.9 Server Discovery

| Method | Server | Protocol |
|---|---|---|
| plex.tv/resources API | Plex | HTTPS (cloud) |
| GDM multicast (port 32412/32414) | Plex | UDP (LAN) |
| Relay fallback | Plex | HTTPS via plex.tv relay |
| Emby Connect | Emby | HTTPS (cloud) |
| Manual URL entry | All | Direct HTTP |
| Quick Connect code | Jellyfin | REST (code-based auth for TV) |

- REQ-MS-26: Plex client MUST support GDM LAN discovery for zero-config local server detection
- REQ-MS-27: Jellyfin Quick Connect MUST be the primary auth flow for TV interfaces (limited input)

