## 5. Streaming UX Best Practices

### 5.1 Recommendation Engine Enhancements

**From Netflix architecture research:**

Current SRS specifies 7 recommendation section types. Research suggests enhancements:

- REQ-REC-01: Cold-start solution: Present 5-tile genre picker at first launch (Sports/Movies/News/Series/Kids), use to seed initial rows
- REQ-REC-02: Adapt recommendations from first 3-5 plays within a session (rapid implicit signal learning)
- REQ-REC-03: Never show an empty home screen — even with zero history, show popularity-based content
- REQ-REC-04: Recommendations MUST be fully independent per profile (no cross-profile contamination)
- REQ-REC-05: TMDB/IMDb enrichment SHOULD be used to supplement provider metadata (posters, ratings, descriptions)
- REQ-REC-06: "Because You Watched [Title]" rows SHOULD explain why content is recommended (transparency builds trust)

### 5.2 Cross-Device Sync Enhancements

- REQ-SYNC-01: Progress sync writes MUST happen on pause, stop, AND every 30 seconds during playback (never wait for app close)
- REQ-SYNC-02: Optimistic local update: update Continue Watching locally immediately, before server acknowledgment
- REQ-SYNC-03: Position granularity MUST be to the second (not rounded to minutes)
- REQ-SYNC-04: Cross-device resume prompt: "You were watching on [device] at [timestamp]. Resume?" with Resume + Start Over options

### 5.3 Casting Support

- REQ-CAST-01: Google Cast button MUST appear in player when Cast device detected (Android)
- REQ-CAST-02: AirPlay route picker MUST appear when AirPlay device detected (iOS/macOS)
- REQ-CAST-03: Cast session MUST preserve watch position for correct resume when cast ends
- REQ-CAST-04: During cast, sender device MUST show a mini-player with play/pause, seek, volume controls

### 5.4 Sports-Specific Features

- REQ-SPORT-01: When EPG genre tag indicates sports event, activate sport-specific UX mode
- REQ-SPORT-02: "Start Over" for live sports MUST be prominently available (sports viewers frequently tune in late)
- REQ-SPORT-03: Multi-game multiview (4-up) with independent audio per quadrant for simultaneous game watching
- REQ-SPORT-04: Game finder view SHOULD show all currently live sports across all sources with scores (if external API available)

### 5.5 Provider Health Dashboard

- REQ-HEALTH-01: Stream health metrics (stall rate, buffer health, TTFF) SHOULD be surfaced per-source in settings
- REQ-HEALTH-02: When a stream fails, the failover reason SHOULD be communicated: "Switched to backup — original stream stalled"
- REQ-HEALTH-03: Provider health history SHOULD be viewable (last 7 days: uptime %, average quality)

