## 6. Accessibility & Compliance

### 6.1 WCAG 2.2 Level AA Requirements for Video Players

| Criterion | Requirement |
|---|---|
| 1.2.2 (A) | Prerecorded video: closed captions |
| 1.2.4 (AA) | Live video: real-time captions |
| 1.2.5 (AA) | Prerecorded video: audio description track |
| 1.4.3 (AA) | Contrast ratio >= 4.5:1 for all UI text |
| 2.1.1 (A) | All player controls keyboard-operable |
| 2.4.3 (A) | Logical focus order through controls |
| 2.4.7 (AA) | Visible keyboard focus indicator |
| 4.1.2 (A) | ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons |
| 4.1.3 (AA) | Status messages (buffering, error) communicated to screen readers |

### 6.2 CVAA (FCC) Requirements

- REQ-A11Y-01: Any television content originally broadcast with captions MUST carry those captions in IP delivery
- REQ-A11Y-02: Caption display controls MUST be accessible to users with disabilities (keyboard, switch access)
- REQ-A11Y-03: Users MUST be able to customize: font size, font style, font color, font opacity, background color, background opacity, window color, window opacity, text edge style
- REQ-A11Y-04: Caption settings MUST persist across sessions
- REQ-A11Y-05: Audio description tracks MUST be selectable by users

### 6.3 Caption Standard Support

| Standard | Format | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| CEA-608 | Line 21 data in MPEG-2 TS | Legacy analog, still in broadcast TS |
| CEA-708 | SEI NAL units in H.264/H.265 | Digital. Rich styling. Required by FCC. |
| WebVTT | Text (in HLS SUBTITLES track) | Native in HLS and browsers |
| SRT | Text (sidecar file) | Widely supported for file playback |
| TTML/IMSC1 | XML (in DASH) | Broadcast-derived OTT content |
| SSA/ASS | Text (sidecar file) | Anime/fansub community standard |

### 6.4 Screen Reader Support

- REQ-A11Y-06: All player controls MUST have meaningful accessibility labels (not generic "Button 1")
- REQ-A11Y-07: Seek bar MUST announce position as "X minutes, Y seconds" (not just a slider percentage)
- REQ-A11Y-08: Error and buffering states MUST be announced via live regions
- REQ-A11Y-09: When VoiceOver/TalkBack is active, audio description track SHOULD be auto-selected if available

### 6.5 Color-Blind Safe Design

- REQ-A11Y-10: Never use color as the sole differentiator — always add shape, icon, or text label
- REQ-A11Y-11: LIVE badge = red dot + "LIVE" text (not just red dot)
- REQ-A11Y-12: Recording scheduled = calendar icon + label (not just green dot)
- REQ-A11Y-13: Progress bars = color fill + percentage text

