## 8. Standards & Compliance Reference

> This section consolidates industry standards, platform requirements, and accessibility minimums. These are non-negotiable constraints from external authorities (WCAG, platform vendors, broadcast standards), separated from design-freedom UX requirements above. Implementations MUST meet these thresholds but MAY exceed them.

### 8.1 Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.2)

| Standard | Level | Requirement | Source |
|---|---|---|---|
| Focus indicator contrast | AA (2.4.7) | Focus indicator MUST have ≥ 3:1 contrast ratio against adjacent colors | WCAG 2.2 |
| Focus indicator area | AAA (2.4.13) | Focus indicator area MUST be ≥ 2px perimeter around the component | WCAG 2.2 |
| Text contrast | AA (1.4.3) | Normal text ≥ 4.5:1 contrast ratio; large text (≥ 18pt) ≥ 3:1 | WCAG 2.2 |
| High contrast mode | AAA | Focus indicator ≥ 7:1 contrast when OS high-contrast mode is active | WCAG 2.2 |
| Touch target size | AA (2.5.8) | Minimum 24×24 CSS px; recommended 44×44dp | WCAG 2.2 / Apple HIG |
| Captions (prerecorded) | A (1.2.2) | Prerecorded video MUST have captions | WCAG 2.2 |
| Captions (live) | AA (1.2.4) | Live video MUST have real-time captions | WCAG 2.2 |
| Audio description | AA (1.2.5) | Prerecorded video MUST offer audio description track | WCAG 2.2 |
| Keyboard operable | A (2.1.1) | All functionality operable via keyboard/D-pad | WCAG 2.2 |
| No keyboard trap | A (2.1.2) | Focus MUST NOT be trapped with no exit path | WCAG 2.2 |

### 8.2 Platform TV Guidelines

| Platform | Minimum Text Size | Minimum Interactive Element | Safe Area / Overscan |
|---|---|---|---|
| Android TV | 24sp body text | 48×48dp focusable area | 48px horizontal, 27px vertical (at 1080p) |
| tvOS (Apple TV) | ~24pt body text | 44×44pt tappable area | 60pt top/bottom, 80pt left/right |
| Fire TV | Same as Android TV | Same as Android TV | Same as Android TV |
| Samsung Tizen | 24px body text | 48×48px | 5% margin all edges |
| LG webOS | 24px body text | 44×44px | 5% margin all edges |
| General TV (10-foot) | Legible from 3 meters | Focusable from 3 meters | 5% margin all edges |

### 8.3 Broadcast & Protocol Standards

| Standard | Requirement | Source |
|---|---|---|
| ETSI EN 300 468 | Color button semantics: Red=destructive, Green=positive, Yellow=toggle, Blue=info | European DVB |
| CEA-608 | Legacy analog closed caption support for broadcast-originated TS content | FCC |
| CEA-708 | Digital closed caption support in H.264/H.265 SEI NAL units | FCC |
| CVAA (FCC) | Caption customization: font, size, color, opacity, background, edge style MUST be user-configurable and persistent | FCC 21st Century CVAA |
| CVAA (FCC) | Audio description tracks MUST be user-selectable | FCC 21st Century CVAA |

### 8.4 Caption Customization (CVAA Mandated)

Users MUST be able to customize the following caption properties (values persist across sessions):

| Property | Options |
|---|---|
| Font family | Multiple options including sans-serif, monospace, casual |
| Font size | Range from small to extra large |
| Text color | Multiple color options |
| Text opacity | Range from transparent to opaque |
| Background color | Multiple color options |
| Background opacity | Range from transparent to opaque |
| Window color | Multiple color options |
| Window opacity | Range from transparent to opaque |
| Text edge style | None, drop shadow, raised, depressed, uniform |

### 8.5 TMDB API Constraints

| Constraint | Value | Source |
|---|---|---|
| Rate limit | 40 requests per 10 seconds | TMDB API Terms |
| Attribution | TMDB logo MUST be displayed when showing TMDB-sourced metadata | TMDB API Terms |
| Image base URL | `https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/{size}/{path}` | TMDB API |
