## 1. Core Product Overview

### 1.1 Product Purpose

CrispyTivi is a **unified multi-source streaming aggregator** that brings together live TV (IPTV), video-on-demand (movies & series), and media server content (Plex, Emby, Jellyfin) into a single, cohesive experience. It runs on 6 platforms: Android (phone, tablet, TV), iOS, macOS, Windows, Linux, and Web.

The application is designed for household use with multi-profile support, parental controls, cloud DVR, and cross-device synchronization. It targets both touch-screen (mobile/tablet) and lean-back (TV with remote control) interaction paradigms.

### 1.2 Core User Flows

#### Flow 1: First-Time Setup (Onboarding)
1. User opens app for the first time
2. Welcome screen introduces the app
3. User adds a content source (M3U URL, Xtream Codes credentials, Stalker portal, or media server login)
4. System verifies credentials / downloads playlist
5. System reports content counts (e.g., "Found 150 channels, 2,400 movies")
6. User creates a profile (name, avatar, optional PIN)
7. User arrives at the home screen with content ready

#### Flow 2: Live TV Viewing
1. User navigates to Live TV
2. Browses channels by category/group or searches
3. Selects a channel to play
4. Full-screen player with OSD (on-screen display) controls
5. Channel zapping via up/down or number entry (TV remote)
6. Views current/next program info from EPG
7. Optionally catches up on past programs (timeshift/catchup)

#### Flow 3: Movie / Series Discovery & Playback
1. User browses Movies or Series sections
2. Filters by genre, sorts by rating/year/recently added
3. Views detail page (synopsis, cast, trailer, ratings)
4. Plays movie or resumes from last position
5. For series: navigates seasons/episodes, auto-plays next episode
6. System tracks watch progress per profile

#### Flow 4: DVR Recording
1. User browses EPG or channel list
2. Selects a program and chooses "Record"
3. Configures recording: one-time or recurring, start/end padding
4. System schedules recording, detects conflicts
5. Recording captured to local or cloud storage
6. User browses completed recordings and plays back

#### Flow 5: Cross-Device Sync
1. User enables cloud sync in settings
2. Watch history, favorites, profiles, and settings sync to cloud (S3-compatible)
3. On another device, user logs in and syncs
4. Merge algorithm resolves conflicts (newer wins)
5. "Continue Watching" shows cross-device progress

#### Flow 6: Multi-Profile Household
1. Parent creates admin profile with PIN
2. Creates child profile with content rating restrictions and source access limits
3. Each profile has independent favorites, watch history, and recommendations
4. Switching profiles requires PIN for protected profiles

#### Flow 7: Multi-Source Aggregation
1. User adds multiple sources (e.g., two IPTV providers + Plex server)
2. All content appears in unified views with source indicator
3. Source selector bar filters by provider
4. Duplicate channels detected and optionally merged
5. EPG priority determined by source sort order

