## 2. UX & Frontend Requirements

> **Design Freedom**: The UI may be completely redesigned. Requirements below define the *experience and value* to deliver, not specific layouts or visual treatments.
>
> **TV-First Philosophy**: This is a TV-first application. Every screen, interaction, and component is designed for a 10-foot lean-back experience with a D-pad remote as the primary input. Touch, mouse, and keyboard are supported but are secondary adaptations of the TV interface — never the other way around. See `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` for the full TV-first design system, spatial navigation requirements, and input device abstraction.
>
> **Unified Library Model**: Movies and series from all sources (IPTV providers, Plex, Emby, Jellyfin) are deduplicated into canonical entities using TMDB IDs. The user sees one collection with "available on" source attribution, not separate silos. See `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` Section 4-6 for full unified library and multi-source live TV requirements.

### 2.1 Platform & Form Factor Support

The application is **TV-first** — the TV experience is the primary design target. Other form factors adapt the TV layout, not the other way around.

| Priority | Form Factor | Input Model | Layout Strategy | Min Interactive Element |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **PRIMARY** | TV / Console (lean-back) | D-pad remote, gamepad, voice | Grid-focused, side navigation rail | 60×60dp, focus ring from 3m |
| Secondary | Desktop / Large (>= 840 dp) | Keyboard + mouse/gamepad/remote | Multi-panel, side navigation | Standard click targets |
| Tertiary | Tablet (medium, 600-840 dp) | Touch (+ optional keyboard) | Two-panel, bottom navigation | 44 x 44 dp |
| Quaternary | Phone (compact, < 600 dp) | Touch | Single-column, bottom navigation | 44 x 44 dp |

**Requirements**:
- REQ-UX-001: Navigation MUST use a side rail (collapsed icon-only ~72dp, expanded icon+label ~256dp) as the primary pattern, adapting to bottom bar only on compact form factors
- REQ-UX-002: All interactive elements MUST be reachable via D-pad navigation — this is the PRIMARY input method, not an alternative
- REQ-UX-003: TV interfaces MUST support color button shortcuts (Red/Green/Yellow/Blue) with a contextual button legend bar (see `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` Section 3.6)
- REQ-UX-004: Content grids MUST reflow columns based on available width (1 → 2 → 4+ columns)
- REQ-UX-005: Modals/dialogs MUST trap focus and be dismissible via Back — full-screen on compact, floating on expanded/TV
- REQ-UX-006: Focus state MUST be visually distinct from typical TV viewing distance using scale, border, and/or shadow — never relying on color alone (see `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` Section 2.3 for behavioral requirements, Section "Standards & Compliance" for contrast minimums)
- REQ-UX-007: System MUST support dark mode natively with semantic color tokens
- REQ-UX-008a: The app MUST implement a spatial focus system with zone-based traversal, focus memory per zone, and directional nearest-neighbor computation (see `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` Section 2)
- REQ-UX-008b: The app MUST implement a unified input abstraction mapping physical buttons to logical actions, supporting remotes, gamepads, keyboards, air mice, and CEC (see `SRS-ADDENDUM-2.md` Section 3)

