| get_vod_categories | `{base}/player_api.php?...&action=get_vod_categories` | Fetch VOD categories |
| get_series_categories | `{base}/player_api.php?...&action=get_series_categories` | Fetch series categories |
| get_live_streams | `{base}/player_api.php?...&action=get_live_streams` | Fetch live channels |
| get_vod_streams | `{base}/player_api.php?...&action=get_vod_streams` | Fetch VOD content |
| get_series | `{base}/player_api.php?...&action=get_series` | Fetch series data |

**Stream URL Patterns**:
- Live: `{base}/live/{user}/{pass}/{stream_id}.ts`
- VOD/Movie: `{base}/movie/{user}/{pass}/{stream_id}.{ext}`
- Series: `{base}/series/{user}/{pass}/{stream_id}.{ext}`
- Catchup: `{base}/timeshift/{user}/{pass}/{duration_min}/{start_utc}/{stream_id}.ts`

**Features**: Catchup support (tv_archive flag + duration), EPG integration, category grouping

#### 5.1.2 Stalker Portal

**Authentication**: Two-step handshake with MAC address + device ID

**Portal Discovery**: Try 4 paths in order:
1. `/stalker_portal/server/load.php`
2. `/portal.php`
3. `/server/load.php`
4. `/c/`

**Auth Flow**:
1. Handshake: `GET ?type=stb&action=handshake&token=` -> returns `{"js":{"token":"..."}}`
2. Do Auth: `GET ?type=stb&action=do_auth&device_id={id}` with `Authorization: Bearer {token}` and `Cookie: mac={encoded_mac}`

**Custom Headers**: `User-Agent: MAG250/1.0 (CrispyTivi)`, `Cookie: mac=...;stb_lang=en;timezone=UTC`

**Content Endpoints**: Paginated results for categories, live streams, VOD, EPG (max 100 pages safety limit)

**Stream URL Resolution**: `?type=stb&action=create_link` returns authenticated stream URL

#### 5.1.3 M3U/M3U8 Playlist

**Format**: Standard M3U8 with `#EXTINF` directives
**EPG Discovery**: `url-tvg` or `x-tvg-url` header attributes
**Catchup Attributes**: `catchup`, `timeshift`, `archive` with duration parameters
**User-Agent Extraction**: `#EXTVLCOPT:http-user-agent=` directives

### 5.2 Media Server Integrations

#### 5.2.1 Plex

**Auth Flow**: OAuth PIN-based
1. POST `https://plex.tv/api/v2/pins` -> get PIN code + ID + expiry (1800s)
2. Open browser to `https://app.plex.tv/auth#?clientID=crispy-tivi&code={pin}`
3. Poll `GET https://plex.tv/api/v2/pins/{pinId}` every 2s until claimed (returns auth token)
4. GET `https://plex.tv/api/v2/resources?includeHttps=1` -> discover servers

**Headers**: `X-Plex-Client-Identifier: crispy-tivi`, `X-Plex-Product: CrispyTivi`, `X-Plex-Token: {authToken}`, `Accept: application/json`

**Server Connection**: Prefers local connections from `connections` array in resources response

#### 5.2.2 Emby & Jellyfin

**Auth Flow**: Similar PIN-based + polling pattern
**Data Source**: Configured HTTP client with auth headers via factory
**Shared Login Screen**: Base component adapted per server type

### 5.3 Cloud Storage (S3-Compatible)

**Purpose**: Cloud backup/sync and DVR recording storage
**Protocol**: S3-compatible HTTP API with XML responses
**Authentication**: AWS Signature Version 4 (HMAC-SHA256 signing)
**Operations**: ListBucket (XML parsing for `<Contents>` entries: Key, Size, LastModified)

### 5.4 External Services

#### 5.4.1 GitHub — Channel Logos

**Repository**: `tv-logo/tv-logos`
**CDN URL**: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tv-logo/tv-logos/main/countries/{dir}/{logo}.png`
**API URL**: `https://api.github.com/repos/tv-logo/tv-logos/contents/countries`
**Directories Scanned**: united-states, international, canada, united-kingdom
**Cache**: 24-hour TTL on logo index

#### 5.4.2 GitHub — App Updates

**Endpoint**: `https://api.github.com/repos/{owner/repo}/releases/latest`
**Process**: Semver comparison, platform-specific asset matching
**Assets**: `.apk` (Android), `.msix`/`.exe` (Windows), `.deb`/`.appimage`/`.tar.gz` (Linux), `.dmg` (macOS)

### 5.5 WebSocket Server (Web Platform)

**Purpose**: Bridge between web frontend and backend engine (since FFI is not available on web)

**Protocol**:
```
Client -> Server: {"cmd": "loadChannels", "id": "req-1", "args": {...}}
Server -> Client: {"id": "req-1", "data": [...]}  (success)
                  {"id": "req-1", "ok": true}      (void success)
                  {"id": "req-1", "error": "..."}   (failure)
```

**Command Categories**: CRUD operations, parser commands, algorithm commands — mirrors the full backend API surface

**Environment**: `CRISPY_DB_PATH` (database file), `CRISPY_PORT` (listen port)

### 5.6 External Player Integration

**Desktop Players**:

| Player | Discovery | Launch Method |
|---|---|---|
| VLC | Well-known paths + PATH | Binary with `--http-user-agent`, `--http-referrer` flags, or `vlc://` scheme |
| mpv | Well-known paths + PATH | Binary with `--force-window=yes`, `--http-header-fields` |
| IINA (macOS) | `/Applications` | `iina://weblink?url=` scheme or `open -a IINA` |
| PotPlayer (Win) | Program Files | `potplayer://` scheme or well-known paths |
| Celluloid (Linux) | PATH | Binary invocation |

**Mobile Players**:

| Player | Android | iOS |
|---|---|---|
| VLC | `vlc://` scheme or intent | `vlc://` scheme |
| MX Player | Intent with title + headers | N/A |
| Kodi | Intent-based | N/A |
| Infuse | N/A | `infuse://x-callback-url/play?url=` |
| JustPlayer | Intent via package | N/A |

**Intent Format** (Android): `intent:{url}#Intent;type=video/*;package={pkg};end`

### 5.7 Platform Permissions

#### Android

| Permission | Purpose |
|---|---|
| INTERNET | Network access for streaming and sync |
| RECORD_AUDIO | Voice search microphone |

| Feature | Required | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| android.hardware.touchscreen | Optional | Support both phone and TV |
| android.software.leanback | Optional | Android TV Leanback launcher |

**Activity Flags**: `supportsPictureInPicture="true"`, `LEANBACK_LAUNCHER` category, hardware acceleration

#### iOS

| Permission | Purpose |
|---|---|
| NSLocalNetworkUsageDescription | AirPlay discovery & streaming |
| NSSpeechRecognitionUsageDescription | Voice search |
| NSMicrophoneUsageDescription | Microphone for voice search |

**Bonjour Services**: `_airplay._tcp` for AirPlay device discovery
**Background Modes**: `audio` for playback continuation
**Network**: `NSAllowsArbitraryLoads: true` (for arbitrary IPTV stream URLs)

#### macOS

- Standard app bundle, no special permissions beyond network access

#### Windows / Linux

- No platform-specific permission declarations required

### 5.8 HTTP Client Configuration

**Standard Profile** (playlist/EPG/stream fetching):
- Connect timeout: 15 seconds
- Total timeout: 120 seconds
- Connection pool: 4 idle per host
- TCP keepalive: 60 seconds
- Redirect limit: 5
- Gzip: enabled
- User-Agent: `CrispyTivi/1.0`

**Fast Profile** (credential verification, URL checks):
- Connect timeout: 5 seconds
- Total timeout: 10 seconds
- Redirect limit: 3
- Same pool and compression settings

**TLS**: Per-source toggle for accepting self-signed certificates (`accept_self_signed` flag)

**Resilience**:
- Retry on transient network failures
- UTF-8 decode with replacement characters for malformed responses
- JSON repair: fix invalid escapes, truncated arrays, missing quotes, lone surrogates
- Gzip auto-decompression

---

## Appendix A: Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| IPTV | Internet Protocol Television — live TV delivered over IP networks |
| M3U/M3U8 | Multimedia playlist format used by IPTV providers |
| Xtream Codes | Popular IPTV management system with standardized API |
| Stalker Portal | Middleware used by MAG set-top boxes for IPTV |
| EPG | Electronic Program Guide — schedule of TV programs |
| XMLTV | XML-based format for TV listings |
| VOD | Video on Demand — movies and series available for streaming |
| DVR | Digital Video Recorder — schedule and record live TV |
| Catchup/Timeshift | Watch past broadcasts from archive |
| PiP | Picture-in-Picture — overlay player on top of other content |
| HDR | High Dynamic Range — enhanced video color/brightness |
| OSD | On-Screen Display — player control overlay |
| BIF | Base Index Frames — thumbnail index format for seek preview |
| VTT | Web Video Text Tracks — subtitle and thumbnail metadata format |
| SigV4 | AWS Signature Version 4 — authentication for S3-compatible storage |
| D-pad | Directional pad — TV remote navigation (up/down/left/right/select) |
| Leanback | Android TV UI framework for lean-back (10-foot) experiences |

## Appendix B: Content Rating Scale

| Value | Rating | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | G | General audiences |
| 1 | PG | Parental guidance suggested |
| 2 | PG-13 | Parents strongly cautioned |
| 3 | R | Restricted |
| 4 | NC-17 | Adults only (no children under 17) |

## Appendix C: DVR Recurrence Bitmask

| Bit | Day | Value |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | Monday | 1 |
| 1 | Tuesday | 2 |
| 2 | Wednesday | 4 |
| 3 | Thursday | 8 |
| 4 | Friday | 16 |
| 5 | Saturday | 32 |
| 6 | Sunday | 64 |

